wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to demolish, to destroy, to wreck","examples":[{"text":"هَدَمَتِ الْجَرَّافَةُ الْبِنَاءَ","english":"The bulldozer has demolished the building."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to demolish, to destroy, to wreck","examples":[{"text":"الَّذِينَ أُخْرِجُوا مِن دِيَارِهِم بِغَيْرِ حَقٍّ إِلَّا أَن يَقُولُوا رَبُّنَا اللّٰهُ وَلَوْلَا دَفْعُ اللّٰهِ النَّاسَ بَعْضَهُم بِبَعْضٍ لَهُدِّمَتْ صَوَامِعُ وَبِيَعٌ وَصَلَوَاتٌ وَمَسَاجِدُ يُذْكَرُ فِيهَا ٱسْمُ اللّٰهِ كَثِيرًا وَلَيَنْصُرَنَّ اللّٰهُ مَن يَنْصُرُهُ إِنَّ اللّٰهَ لَقَوِيٌّ عَزِيزٌ","english":"[They are] those who have been evicted from their homes without right – only because they say, “Our Lord is Allah.” And were it not that Allah checks the people, some by means of others, there would have been demolished monasteries, churches, synagogues, and mosques in which the name of Allah is much mentioned. And Allah will surely support those who support Him. Indeed, Allah is Powerful and Exalted in Might."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of هَدَمَ (hadama)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"demolition"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ha.da.ma/","/hadm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44254","headword_ar":"هَدَمَ","root":"hdm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a building; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulled"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to pieces; demolished"},{"kind":"text","text":"it;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed"},{"kind":"text","text":"it: (K:) [the last two explanations are the most correct, as is shown by the phrase]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqaDa AlbinaA='a mino Eayori hadomi","text_ar":"نَقَضَ البِنَا=ءَ مِنْ عَيْرِ هَدْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took to pieces the building without demolishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroying"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A, Msb, K, * in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwD","text_ar":"قوض"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ruined"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a building, &c.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reduced"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to ruin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham, p. 31.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]}]}}